CTE - Common Table Expressions ==> Temporary, named result set(virtual table), that can be used multiple times within query
to simplify and organize complex query.

Note:- ORDER BY clause is invalid in views,inline functions,derived tables,subqueries & CTEs.. you can use ORDER BY clause in 
Main query.

How CTE executed in DB:- CTE resultset is stored in cache.. every time main query needs it takes data from cache.

CTE Types 1. None recursive CTE ===> i. Standalone CTE ii. Nested CTE
2. Recursive CTE

1. Standlone CTE :- doesn't depend on anything.
syntax:- 
WITH <cte_name> AS (SELECT ... FROM... WHERE ....)   --CTE query
SELECT .... FROM <cte_name> WHERE......              --Main query 

--find the total sales per customer
--Common Table Expression CTE
WITH cte_totalsales_customer AS
(
SELECT
CustomerID,
SUM(sales) Total_sales
FROM Sales.Orders
GROUP BY CustomerID
)
--Main Query
SELECT 
c.CustomerID,
c.FirstName,
c.LastName,
cte.Total_sales 
FROM Sales.Customers c LEFT JOIN cte_totalsales_customer cte
ON c.CustomerID=cte.CustomerID
ORDER BY cte.Total_sales DESC


